text:
Super duper traditional kind of western food. It has those old school taste that you rarely find nowadays.

Ordered the chicken cutlet at 8.50, got fries, coleslaw, red beans, a huge slab of cutlet, and 2 packets of chilli sauce.

Personally, I found the cutlet to be huge, but unfortunately there was no sauce to complement it. Some stalls will provide tartar / mayo sauce.

Taste wise was so so. Red beans are chilled, which is something new to me as usually they are served hot. But I kind of liked it.

Came across this stall and supported the old couples. Their food I would say are fresh and old school kind. I feel the price not worth as both fish and chip are very thin. Payment only by cash.
Fish and chip: crispy, ginger taste abit strong
Chicken cutlets: crispy and good.

First time ordering. The fish n chips is tasty.

Very crispy type. If bigger slice will be even better

Price $7.50

Wanted to change the side dishes to sunny egg but owner say no changes. Waiting time is about 10mins.

Look at size of the pork chop slab! Would consider it reasonable value for money at $7.50. It was cooked just right, tender & juicy. The fries are freshly deep-fried, & coleslaw has a slight tangy-ness to it, yummy! Friendly stallholders, offering old school style dishes. Service is considered fast as dish is only cooked upon order. Came at off-peak hours post lunch, no crowd or queue. Do support them when in the area!

It used to be at Blk 327 HG A5 coffeeshop for years before relocated to 4 Defu Lane 10.

Personal preference:
Fried Chicken Wings
Chicken Chop
Chicken Chop Fried Rice.
